projects.description:
Last weekend, Samuel Khang and I had the opportunity to participate and win the 🏆 Best AI Application built with Cloudflare at #Hacklytics2025, hosted by Data Science @ GT! 

Sam and I personally have had trouble with pain and injury with our squat forms at the gym. That's why, over the weekend, we built 🏋️‍ SquatSpot, an AI-powered squat analysis tool that provides real-time feedback on weightlifting form!

SquatSpot analyzes your squat form with 11+ biomechanical metrics in real-time through your camera or uploaded videos. It compares your form against both a population of elite lifters and any video of your choice, and gives you a calculated similarity score. SquatSpot also provides personalized AI feedback on how to improve your form by tracking your progress over multiple reps and identifies specific areas for improvement. 

🚀 Technologies Used:

- Computer Vision Engine: Used MediaPipe and OpenCV to track 33 body landmarks in real-time for precise pose estimation
- AI Feedback: Integrated Cloudflare Workers AI with LLaMA 3.1 to generate personalized form corrections
- React + Flask Stack: Built responsive frontend in React.js with a Flask backend for seamless video processing and metric analysis

A huge thank you to #Hacklytics2025 and the organizational team for a great weekend!

✅ Check out the project here:
Github - https://lnkd.in/eGKJUmne
Devpost Submission - https://lnkd.in/eryxnvtb

projects.description:
- Developed a software to use LLMs for extracting context from hundreds of thousands of Electronic Health Records.
- Integrated the context into an embedded vector space to house and sort patients by overall similarity.
- Leveraged macro patient trends to treat specific rare conditions by providing predictions of future symptoms and suggest relevant medicine

- Developed a Quantum Generative Adversarial Network (QGAN) model coupled with a classical optimizer to demonstrate that qubits with a high fidelity can be achieved on Noisy Intermediate-Scale Quantum (NISQ) hardware using Quandela’s quantum photonic chip.
- Results show that the model configuration is feasible even under conditions where up to 50% of the QGAN’s generator’s phase shifters are damaged and the discriminator’s phase shifters are subjected to phase noise up to 0.04π.
